{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018YA9XcNqVHNL5CdwFsjopH","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→import { PublicKey, TransactionInstruction, SystemProgram } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\n     2→import { Tier } from \"./types\";\n     3→\n     4→// Placeholder program ID - will be replaced with actual deployed program\n     5→const POOL_MANAGER_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\n     6→  \"11111111111111111111111111111111\"\n     7→);\n     8→\n     9→export interface EntryParams {\n    10→  player: PublicKey;\n    11→  gameId: string;\n    12→  roundId: string;\n    13→  tier: Tier;\n    14→}\n    15→\n    16→export interface CashoutParams {\n    17→  player: PublicKey;\n    18→  gameId: string;\n    19→  roundId: string;\n    20→}\n    21→\n    22→/**\n    23→ * Build instruction for entering a game pool\n    24→ * NOTE: This is a placeholder. Actual implementation depends on deployed program.\n    25→ */\n    26→export function buildEntryInstruction(params: EntryParams): TransactionInstruction {\n    27→  const { player, gameId, roundId, tier } = params;\n    28→  // Note: TIER_AMOUNTS[tier] will be used for instruction data in full implementation\n    29→\n    30→  // Derive pool PDA\n    31→  const [poolPda] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    32→    [\n    33→      Buffer.from(\"pool\"),\n    34→      Buffer.from(gameId),\n    35→      Buffer.from(roundId),\n    36→      Buffer.from(tier),\n    37→    ],\n    38→    POOL_MANAGER_PROGRAM_ID\n    39→  );\n    40→\n    41→  // Derive player entry PDA\n    42→  const [entryPda] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    43→    [Buffer.from(\"entry\"), poolPda.toBuffer(), player.toBuffer()],\n    44→    POOL_MANAGER_PROGRAM_ID\n    45→  );\n    46→\n    47→  // Placeholder instruction - actual data layout depends on Anchor IDL\n    48→  return new TransactionInstruction({\n    49→    keys: [\n    50→      { pubkey: player, isSigner: true, isWritable: true },\n    51→      { pubkey: poolPda, isSigner: false, isWritable: true },\n    52→      { pubkey: entryPda, isSigner: false, isWritable: true },\n    53→      { pubkey: SystemProgram.programId, isSigner: false, isWritable: false },\n    54→    ],\n    55→    programId: POOL_MANAGER_PROGRAM_ID,\n    56→    data: Buffer.from([]), // Placeholder\n    57→  });\n    58→}\n    59→\n    60→/**\n    61→ * Build instruction for cashing out (Crash game)\n    62→ * NOTE: This is a placeholder. Actual implementation depends on deployed program.\n    63→ */\n    64→export function buildCashoutInstruction(\n    65→  params: CashoutParams\n    66→): TransactionInstruction {\n    67→  const { player, gameId, roundId } = params;\n    68→\n    69→  const [poolPda] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    70→    [Buffer.from(\"pool\"), Buffer.from(gameId), Buffer.from(roundId)],\n    71→    POOL_MANAGER_PROGRAM_ID\n    72→  );\n    73→\n    74→  const [entryPda] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    75→    [Buffer.from(\"entry\"), poolPda.toBuffer(), player.toBuffer()],\n    76→    POOL_MANAGER_PROGRAM_ID\n    77→  );\n    78→\n    79→  return new TransactionInstruction({\n    80→    keys: [\n    81→      { pubkey: player, isSigner: true, isWritable: true },\n    82→      { pubkey: poolPda, isSigner: false, isWritable: true },\n    83→      { pubkey: entryPda, isSigner: false, isWritable: true },\n    84→    ],\n    85→    programId: POOL_MANAGER_PROGRAM_ID,\n    86→    data: Buffer.from([]), // Placeholder\n    87→  });\n    88→}\n    89→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JvKj8yFv1VCGKHF516Dvye","session_id":"d59010d9-1bac-40d3-83bc-cafa01465d5f","uuid":"09591e6a-ffe9-44e8-ac34-fc382b1656a8"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JvKj8yFv1VCGKHF516Dvye","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a complete picture. Let me create a comprehensive report of the verification architecture.\n\n## Completion Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the verification implementation across the codebase. Here's what I found:\n\n---\n\n## Package Architecture Overview\n\n### **1. `@rng-utopia/fairness` Package** (`packages/fairness/`)\nThis is a standalone fairness verification package using `@noble/hashes` for cryptographic operations.\n\n**Structure:**\n```\npackages/fairness/src/\n├── commitment.ts      # SHA-256 commitment scheme\n├── crash.ts          # HMAC-based crash point calculation\n├── verification.ts   # Main verification orchestrator\n└── index.ts         # Public exports\n```\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- `@noble/hashes` (v1.6.0) - cryptographic primitives\n\n---\n\n### **2. `@rng-utopia/game-engine` Package** (`packages/game-engine/`)\nContains game-specific logic, PDA derivation, and winner determination functions.\n\n**Structure:**\n```\npackages/game-engine/src/\n├── coinflip.ts           # Coinflip PDAs + winner logic\n├── lordofrngs.ts         # Lord of RNGs PDAs + winner logic\n├── types.ts              # Shared types/constants\n├── payouts.ts            # Payout calculations (UI verification only)\n├── RoundStateMachine.ts  # Phase management\n├── GameEventEmitter.ts   # Event system\n├── instructions.ts       # Legacy instruction builders\n├── browser.ts           # Browser-safe exports (no Buffer)\n└── index.ts             # Main exports\n```\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- `@solana/web3.js` (v1.98.0)\n\n---\n\n## How Coinflip Verification Works\n\n### **File: `packages/game-engine/src/coinflip.ts`**\n\n**Key Functions:**\n\n1. **`determineWinnerFromRandomness(randomness: Uint8Array, player1Side: CoinSide)`**\n   - Takes VRF randomness bytes\n   - Uses first byte: `firstByte % 2 === 0 ? \"heads\" : \"tails\"`\n   - Compares result to player1's chosen side\n   - Returns: `{ result: CoinSide, player1Wins: boolean }`\n\n2. **PDA Derivation:**\n   - `getMatchPda(creator)` - seeds: `[\"match\", creator.toBytes()]`\n   - `getConfigPda()` - seeds: `[\"coinflip_config\"]`\n\n3. **Helper Functions:**\n   - `getEntryAmount(tier)` - maps tier to SOL amount\n   - `calculatePotentialPayout(tier)` - computes winner payout (2x entry - 3% fee)\n   - `getOppositeSide(side)` - flips heads/tails\n\n---\n\n## How Lord of RNGs Should Mirror This\n\n### **File: `packages/game-engine/src/lordofrngs.ts`** (Current State)\n\n**Already Implemented:**\n\n1. **PDA Derivation:**\n   ```typescript\n   getRoundPda(tier: number, roundNumber: bigint | number)\n   // Seeds: [\"jackpot_round\", tier (1 byte LE), round_number (8 bytes LE)]\n   \n   getConfigPda()\n   // Seeds: [\"lord_config\"]\n   ```\n\n2. **Winner Determination:**\n   ```typescript\n   determineWinnerFromRandomness(\n     randomness: Uint8Array,\n     totalEntries: number,\n     players: LordPlayerEntry[]\n   ): { winningSlot: number, winner: PublicKey }\n   ```\n\n   **Logic:**\n   - Reads first 8 bytes as little-endian u64\n   - Computes `raw % totalEntries` to get winning slot\n   - Maps slot to player using `mapSlotToPlayer()`\n\n3. **Slot Mapping:**\n   ```typescript\n   mapSlotToPlayer(winningSlot: number, players: LordPlayerEntry[])\n   ```\n   - Players own contiguous ranges\n   - Player 0: slots [0, entries0)\n   - Player 1: slots [entries0, entries0+entries1)\n   - etc.\n\n---\n\n## What's Missing for Lord of RNGs Verification\n\n**Comparing to Coinflip:**\n\n| Feature | Coinflip | Lord of RNGs | Status |\n|---------|----------|--------------|--------|\n| Program ID constant | ✅ `COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID` | ✅ `LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID` | **Complete** |\n| PDA derivation | ✅ `getMatchPda`, `getConfigPda` | ✅ `getRoundPda`, `getConfigPda` | **Complete** |\n| Entry amount | ✅ `getEntryAmount(tier)` | ✅ `getLordEntryAmount(tier)` | **Complete** |\n| Winner from randomness | ✅ `determineWinnerFromRandomness` | ✅ `determineWinnerFromRandomness` | **Complete** |\n| Slot mapping | N/A | ✅ `mapSlotToPlayer` | **Complete** |\n| Payout calculation | ✅ `calculatePotentialPayout` | ❌ **Missing** | **Needs Implementation** |\n\n---\n\n## Recommended Implementation for Lord of RNGs\n\n### **Add to `packages/game-engine/src/lordofrngs.ts`:**\n\n```typescript\n/**\n * Calculate total jackpot (all entries minus 3% fee)\n * Similar to coinflip's calculatePotentialPayout but for N players\n */\nexport function calculateJackpotPayout(\n  tier: Tier,\n  totalEntries: number\n): number {\n  const entryAmount = TIER_AMOUNTS[tier];\n  const totalPool = entryAmount * totalEntries;\n  const fee = Math.floor(totalPool * 0.03);\n  return totalPool - fee;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Fairness Package Architecture\n\n### **File: `packages/fairness/src/verification.ts`**\n\nThis is the **orchestrator** that combines commitment and outcome verification:\n\n```typescript\ninterface RoundData {\n  roundId: string;\n  gameId: string;\n  serverSeed: string;    // Revealed after round\n  publicSeed: string;    // Known upfront\n  commitment: string;    // SHA-256(serverSeed), published upfront\n  claimedOutcome: number;\n}\n\ninterface VerificationResult {\n  valid: boolean;\n  errors: string[];\n  computedOutcome?: number;\n}\n\nverifyRound(round: RoundData): VerificationResult\n```\n\n**Verification Steps:**\n1. ✅ `verifyCommitment(serverSeed, commitment)` - ensures seed wasn't changed\n2. ✅ `computeCrashPoint(serverSeed, publicSeed, roundId, gameId)` - recomputes outcome\n3. ✅ Compares computed vs claimed outcome (with 0.01 tolerance for floats)\n\n---\n\n### **File: `packages/fairness/src/commitment.ts`**\n\n```typescript\ncomputeCommitment(serverSeed: string): string\n// Returns: sha256(serverSeed) as hex\n\nverifyCommitment(serverSeed: string, commitment: string): boolean\n// Returns: true if computed commitment matches provided one\n```\n\n---\n\n### **File: `packages/fairness/src/crash.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nhashToCrashPoint(hashHex: string): number\n// Takes first 52 bits (13 hex chars) of hash\n// Formula: floor((100 * 2^52 - h) / (2^52 - h)) / 100\n// Result: [1.00, ~∞] with ~50% chance ≤ 2x\n\ncomputeCrashPoint(serverSeed, publicSeed, roundId, gameId): number\n// HMAC-SHA256(serverSeed, \"publicSeed:roundId:gameId\")\n// Then hashToCrashPoint(hash)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Key Insights for Lord of RNGs\n\n### **1. Coinflip Uses Ephemeral VRF (MagicBlock/Orao)**\n- Randomness comes from on-chain VRF (not HMAC)\n- `determineWinnerFromRandomness()` just reads the VRF bytes\n- No commitment scheme needed (VRF itself is provably fair)\n\n### **2. Crash Uses HMAC Seed Chain**\n- Off-chain server commits to `sha256(serverSeed)` upfront\n- After round, reveals `serverSeed`\n- Players verify: commitment matches + recompute crash point\n- This is what the `@rng-utopia/fairness` package is designed for\n\n### **3. Lord of RNGs Should Use VRF (Like Coinflip)**\n- Since it's using Orao VRF (per your spec), verification is simpler\n- **You don't need commitment/HMAC verification**\n- **You just need to:**\n  1. ✅ Read VRF randomness from on-chain account\n  2. ✅ Recompute winner using `determineWinnerFromRandomness()`\n  3. ✅ Verify winner matches on-chain result\n\n---\n\n## Export Analysis\n\n### **`packages/game-engine/src/index.ts` Exports:**\n\n```typescript\n// Coinflip exports\nexport {\n  COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID,\n  getMatchPda,\n  getConfigPda,\n  getEntryAmount,\n  calculatePotentialPayout,  // ← Coinflip has this\n  getOppositeSide,\n  determineWinnerFromRandomness,\n} from \"./coinflip\";\n\n// Lord of RNGs exports\nexport {\n  LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID,\n  getRoundPda,\n  getConfigPda as getLordConfigPda,\n  getLordEntryAmount,\n  determineWinnerFromRandomness as determineLordWinnerFromRandomness,\n  mapSlotToPlayer,\n  type LordPlayerEntry,\n} from \"./lordofrngs\";\n```\n\n**Missing from Lord exports:**\n- ❌ `calculateJackpotPayout` (equivalent to `calculatePotentialPayout`)\n\n---\n\n## Files Read (All Absolute Paths)\n\n1. **Game Engine Package:**\n   - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/src/index.ts`\n   - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/src/coinflip.ts`\n   - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/src/lordofrngs.ts`\n   - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/src/types.ts`\n   - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/src/payouts.ts`\n   - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/src/RoundStateMachine.ts`\n   - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/src/GameEventEmitter.ts`\n   - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/src/browser.ts`\n   - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/src/instructions.ts`\n   - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/package.json`\n\n2. **Fairness Package:**\n   - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/fairness/src/index.ts`\n   - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/fairness/src/verification.ts`\n   - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/fairness/src/commitment.ts`\n   - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/fairness/src/crash.ts`\n   - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/fairness/package.json`\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n**Coinflip verification is VRF-based** (no commitment scheme needed):\n- ✅ Get randomness from VRF\n- ✅ Call `determineWinnerFromRandomness()`\n- ✅ Compare to on-chain result\n\n**Lord of RNGs already has the core verification** but is missing:\n- ❌ `calculateJackpotPayout()` function (should compute `totalPool * 0.97`)\n- ❌ Export of the new payout function from `index.ts`\n\n**The `@rng-utopia/fairness` package is for HMAC-based games** (like Crash), not VRF games (like Coinflip/Lord of RNGs). You don't need it for Lord of RNGs verification."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a5cb868 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 44497\ntool_uses: 25\nduration_ms: 106479</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d59010d9-1bac-40d3-83bc-cafa01465d5f","uuid":"6b002556-40bc-41fe-bd9e-63589d7c91df","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand how coinflip verification works to mirror it for Lord of the RNGs. Please explore:\n\n1. `sources/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/src/` - look for verification.ts or any verification-related files\n2. `sources/rng-utopia/packages/fairness/src/` - look for all files and the package structure\n3. `sources/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/src/coinflip.ts` - look for verification functions\n4. `sources/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/src/index.ts` - see all exports\n5. `sources/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/src/lordofrngs.ts` - see what's already been created\n\nFor each file, show the full contents. Be thorough.","agentId":"a5cb868","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a complete picture. Let me create a comprehensive report of the verification architecture.\n\n## Completion Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the verification implementation across the codebase. Here's what I found:\n\n---\n\n## Package Architecture Overview\n\n### **1. `@rng-utopia/fairness` Package** (`packages/fairness/`)\nThis is a standalone fairness verification package using `@noble/hashes` for cryptographic operations.\n\n**Structure:**\n```\npackages/fairness/src/\n├── commitment.ts      # SHA-256 commitment scheme\n├── crash.ts          # HMAC-based crash point calculation\n├── verification.ts   # Main verification orchestrator\n└── index.ts         # Public exports\n```\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- `@noble/hashes` (v1.6.0) - cryptographic primitives\n\n---\n\n### **2. `@rng-utopia/game-engine` Package** (`packages/game-engine/`)\nContains game-specific logic, PDA derivation, and winner determination functions.\n\n**Structure:**\n```\npackages/game-engine/src/\n├── coinflip.ts           # Coinflip PDAs + winner logic\n├── lordofrngs.ts         # Lord of RNGs PDAs + winner logic\n├── types.ts              # Shared types/constants\n├── payouts.ts            # Payout calculations (UI verification only)\n├── RoundStateMachine.ts  # Phase management\n├── GameEventEmitter.ts   # Event system\n├── instructions.ts       # Legacy instruction builders\n├── browser.ts           # Browser-safe exports (no Buffer)\n└── index.ts             # Main exports\n```\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- `@solana/web3.js` (v1.98.0)\n\n---\n\n## How Coinflip Verification Works\n\n### **File: `packages/game-engine/src/coinflip.ts`**\n\n**Key Functions:**\n\n1. **`determineWinnerFromRandomness(randomness: Uint8Array, player1Side: CoinSide)`**\n   - Takes VRF randomness bytes\n   - Uses first byte: `firstByte % 2 === 0 ? \"heads\" : \"tails\"`\n   - Compares result to player1's chosen side\n   - Returns: `{ result: CoinSide, player1Wins: boolean }`\n\n2. **PDA Derivation:**\n   - `getMatchPda(creator)` - seeds: `[\"match\", creator.toBytes()]`\n   - `getConfigPda()` - seeds: `[\"coinflip_config\"]`\n\n3. **Helper Functions:**\n   - `getEntryAmount(tier)` - maps tier to SOL amount\n   - `calculatePotentialPayout(tier)` - computes winner payout (2x entry - 3% fee)\n   - `getOppositeSide(side)` - flips heads/tails\n\n---\n\n## How Lord of RNGs Should Mirror This\n\n### **File: `packages/game-engine/src/lordofrngs.ts`** (Current State)\n\n**Already Implemented:**\n\n1. **PDA Derivation:**\n   ```typescript\n   getRoundPda(tier: number, roundNumber: bigint | number)\n   // Seeds: [\"jackpot_round\", tier (1 byte LE), round_number (8 bytes LE)]\n   \n   getConfigPda()\n   // Seeds: [\"lord_config\"]\n   ```\n\n2. **Winner Determination:**\n   ```typescript\n   determineWinnerFromRandomness(\n     randomness: Uint8Array,\n     totalEntries: number,\n     players: LordPlayerEntry[]\n   ): { winningSlot: number, winner: PublicKey }\n   ```\n\n   **Logic:**\n   - Reads first 8 bytes as little-endian u64\n   - Computes `raw % totalEntries` to get winning slot\n   - Maps slot to player using `mapSlotToPlayer()`\n\n3. **Slot Mapping:**\n   ```typescript\n   mapSlotToPlayer(winningSlot: number, players: LordPlayerEntry[])\n   ```\n   - Players own contiguous ranges\n   - Player 0: slots [0, entries0)\n   - Player 1: slots [entries0, entries0+entries1)\n   - etc.\n\n---\n\n## What's Missing for Lord of RNGs Verification\n\n**Comparing to Coinflip:**\n\n| Feature | Coinflip | Lord of RNGs | Status |\n|---------|----------|--------------|--------|\n| Program ID constant | ✅ `COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID` | ✅ `LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID` | **Complete** |\n| PDA derivation | ✅ `getMatchPda`, `getConfigPda` | ✅ `getRoundPda`, `getConfigPda` | **Complete** |\n| Entry amount | ✅ `getEntryAmount(tier)` | ✅ `getLordEntryAmount(tier)` | **Complete** |\n| Winner from randomness | ✅ `determineWinnerFromRandomness` | ✅ `determineWinnerFromRandomness` | **Complete** |\n| Slot mapping | N/A | ✅ `mapSlotToPlayer` | **Complete** |\n| Payout calculation | ✅ `calculatePotentialPayout` | ❌ **Missing** | **Needs Implementation** |\n\n---\n\n## Recommended Implementation for Lord of RNGs\n\n### **Add to `packages/game-engine/src/lordofrngs.ts`:**\n\n```typescript\n/**\n * Calculate total jackpot (all entries minus 3% fee)\n * Similar to coinflip's calculatePotentialPayout but for N players\n */\nexport function calculateJackpotPayout(\n  tier: Tier,\n  totalEntries: number\n): number {\n  const entryAmount = TIER_AMOUNTS[tier];\n  const totalPool = entryAmount * totalEntries;\n  const fee = Math.floor(totalPool * 0.03);\n  return totalPool - fee;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Fairness Package Architecture\n\n### **File: `packages/fairness/src/verification.ts`**\n\nThis is the **orchestrator** that combines commitment and outcome verification:\n\n```typescript\ninterface RoundData {\n  roundId: string;\n  gameId: string;\n  serverSeed: string;    // Revealed after round\n  publicSeed: string;    // Known upfront\n  commitment: string;    // SHA-256(serverSeed), published upfront\n  claimedOutcome: number;\n}\n\ninterface VerificationResult {\n  valid: boolean;\n  errors: string[];\n  computedOutcome?: number;\n}\n\nverifyRound(round: RoundData): VerificationResult\n```\n\n**Verification Steps:**\n1. ✅ `verifyCommitment(serverSeed, commitment)` - ensures seed wasn't changed\n2. ✅ `computeCrashPoint(serverSeed, publicSeed, roundId, gameId)` - recomputes outcome\n3. ✅ Compares computed vs claimed outcome (with 0.01 tolerance for floats)\n\n---\n\n### **File: `packages/fairness/src/commitment.ts`**\n\n```typescript\ncomputeCommitment(serverSeed: string): string\n// Returns: sha256(serverSeed) as hex\n\nverifyCommitment(serverSeed: string, commitment: string): boolean\n// Returns: true if computed commitment matches provided one\n```\n\n---\n\n### **File: `packages/fairness/src/crash.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nhashToCrashPoint(hashHex: string): number\n// Takes first 52 bits (13 hex chars) of hash\n// Formula: floor((100 * 2^52 - h) / (2^52 - h)) / 100\n// Result: [1.00, ~∞] with ~50% chance ≤ 2x\n\ncomputeCrashPoint(serverSeed, publicSeed, roundId, gameId): number\n// HMAC-SHA256(serverSeed, \"publicSeed:roundId:gameId\")\n// Then hashToCrashPoint(hash)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Key Insights for Lord of RNGs\n\n### **1. Coinflip Uses Ephemeral VRF (MagicBlock/Orao)**\n- Randomness comes from on-chain VRF (not HMAC)\n- `determineWinnerFromRandomness()` just reads the VRF bytes\n- No commitment scheme needed (VRF itself is provably fair)\n\n### **2. Crash Uses HMAC Seed Chain**\n- Off-chain server commits to `sha256(serverSeed)` upfront\n- After round, reveals `serverSeed`\n- Players verify: commitment matches + recompute crash point\n- This is what the `@rng-utopia/fairness` package is designed for\n\n### **3. Lord of RNGs Should Use VRF (Like Coinflip)**\n- Since it's using Orao VRF (per your spec), verification is simpler\n- **You don't need commitment/HMAC verification**\n- **You just need to:**\n  1. ✅ Read VRF randomness from on-chain account\n  2. ✅ Recompute winner using `determineWinnerFromRandomness()`\n  3. ✅ Verify winner matches on-chain result\n\n---\n\n## Export Analysis\n\n### **`packages/game-engine/src/index.ts` Exports:**\n\n```typescript\n// Coinflip exports\nexport {\n  COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID,\n  getMatchPda,\n  getConfigPda,\n  getEntryAmount,\n  calculatePotentialPayout,  // ← Coinflip has this\n  getOppositeSide,\n  determineWinnerFromRandomness,\n} from \"./coinflip\";\n\n// Lord of RNGs exports\nexport {\n  LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID,\n  getRoundPda,\n  getConfigPda as getLordConfigPda,\n  getLordEntryAmount,\n  determineWinnerFromRandomness as determineLordWinnerFromRandomness,\n  mapSlotToPlayer,\n  type LordPlayerEntry,\n} from \"./lordofrngs\";\n```\n\n**Missing from Lord exports:**\n- ❌ `calculateJackpotPayout` (equivalent to `calculatePotentialPayout`)\n\n---\n\n## Files Read (All Absolute Paths)\n\n1. **Game Engine Package:**\n   - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/src/index.ts`\n   - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/src/coinflip.ts`\n   - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/src/lordofrngs.ts`\n   - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/src/types.ts`\n   - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/src/payouts.ts`\n   - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/src/RoundStateMachine.ts`\n   - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/src/GameEventEmitter.ts`\n   - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/src/browser.ts`\n   - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/src/instructions.ts`\n   - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/package.json`\n\n2. **Fairness Package:**\n   - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/fairness/src/index.ts`\n   - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/fairness/src/verification.ts`\n   - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/fairness/src/commitment.ts`\n   - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/fairness/src/crash.ts`\n   - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/fairness/package.json`\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n**Coinflip verification is VRF-based** (no commitment scheme needed):\n- ✅ Get randomness from VRF\n- ✅ Call `determineWinnerFromRandomness()`\n- ✅ Compare to on-chain result\n\n**Lord of RNGs already has the core verification** but is missing:\n- ❌ `calculateJackpotPayout()` function (should compute `totalPool * 0.97`)\n- ❌ Export of the new payout function from `index.ts`\n\n**The `@rng-utopia/fairness` package is for HMAC-based games** (like Crash), not VRF games (like Coinflip/Lord of RNGs). You don't need it for Lord of RNGs verification."}],"totalDurationMs":106479,"totalTokens":44497,"totalToolUseCount":25,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1890,"cache_read_input_tokens":39319,"output_tokens":3281,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1890,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
