{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013JTTtYw7sJ35T8Q32VkE4h","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→import { verifyCommitment } from \"./commitment\";\n     2→import { computeCrashPoint } from \"./crash\";\n     3→\n     4→export interface RoundData {\n     5→  roundId: string;\n     6→  gameId: string;\n     7→  serverSeed: string;\n     8→  publicSeed: string;\n     9→  commitment: string;\n    10→  claimedOutcome: number;\n    11→}\n    12→\n    13→export interface VerificationResult {\n    14→  valid: boolean;\n    15→  errors: string[];\n    16→  computedOutcome?: number;\n    17→}\n    18→\n    19→/**\n    20→ * Verify a completed round's fairness\n    21→ * Checks:\n    22→ * 1. Server seed matches commitment\n    23→ * 2. Computed outcome matches claimed outcome\n    24→ */\n    25→export function verifyRound(round: RoundData): VerificationResult {\n    26→  const errors: string[] = [];\n    27→\n    28→  // Verify commitment\n    29→  const commitmentValid = verifyCommitment(round.serverSeed, round.commitment);\n    30→  if (!commitmentValid) {\n    31→    errors.push(\"Server seed does not match commitment\");\n    32→  }\n    33→\n    34→  // Compute expected outcome\n    35→  const computedOutcome = computeCrashPoint(\n    36→    round.serverSeed,\n    37→    round.publicSeed,\n    38→    round.roundId,\n    39→    round.gameId\n    40→  );\n    41→\n    42→  // Check outcome matches (with small tolerance for floating point)\n    43→  const tolerance = 0.01;\n    44→  if (Math.abs(computedOutcome - round.claimedOutcome) > tolerance) {\n    45→    errors.push(\n    46→      `Computed outcome (${computedOutcome.toFixed(2)}) does not match claimed outcome (${round.claimedOutcome.toFixed(2)})`\n    47→    );\n    48→  }\n    49→\n    50→  return {\n    51→    valid: errors.length === 0,\n    52→    errors,\n    53→    computedOutcome,\n    54→  };\n    55→}\n    56→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d59010d9-1bac-40d3-83bc-cafa01465d5f","uuid":"fc178bcf-3933-46b6-9291-3cbc2ebb913b","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/fairness/src/verification.ts","content":"import { verifyCommitment } from \"./commitment\";\nimport { computeCrashPoint } from \"./crash\";\n\nexport interface RoundData {\n  roundId: string;\n  gameId: string;\n  serverSeed: string;\n  publicSeed: string;\n  commitment: string;\n  claimedOutcome: number;\n}\n\nexport interface VerificationResult {\n  valid: boolean;\n  errors: string[];\n  computedOutcome?: number;\n}\n\n/**\n * Verify a completed round's fairness\n * Checks:\n * 1. Server seed matches commitment\n * 2. Computed outcome matches claimed outcome\n */\nexport function verifyRound(round: RoundData): VerificationResult {\n  const errors: string[] = [];\n\n  // Verify commitment\n  const commitmentValid = verifyCommitment(round.serverSeed, round.commitment);\n  if (!commitmentValid) {\n    errors.push(\"Server seed does not match commitment\");\n  }\n\n  // Compute expected outcome\n  const computedOutcome = computeCrashPoint(\n    round.serverSeed,\n    round.publicSeed,\n    round.roundId,\n    round.gameId\n  );\n\n  // Check outcome matches (with small tolerance for floating point)\n  const tolerance = 0.01;\n  if (Math.abs(computedOutcome - round.claimedOutcome) > tolerance) {\n    errors.push(\n      `Computed outcome (${computedOutcome.toFixed(2)}) does not match claimed outcome (${round.claimedOutcome.toFixed(2)})`\n    );\n  }\n\n  return {\n    valid: errors.length === 0,\n    errors,\n    computedOutcome,\n  };\n}\n","numLines":56,"startLine":1,"totalLines":56}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01AbALinnTCj8KB7a6xDBQA7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I understand the full picture. The checklist item says:\n\n> **[engine] Add Lord of the RNGs verification function** to `packages/game-engine/src/` or `packages/fairness/src/` — given a tx signature, extract RoundSettled event, re-derive winning_slot from randomness, verify it matches the event's winner. Pattern: mirror coinflip `verification.ts`. Verify: TypeScript compiles.\n\nThe fairness package is HMAC/crash-specific. For VRF-based games (coinflip, lord), verification belongs in game-engine. The checklist says \"mirror coinflip `verification.ts`\" — but coinflip doesn't have a separate `verification.ts`. The verification is just `determineWinnerFromRandomness`. \n\nWhat we need is a function that takes a `RoundSettled` event's data and re-derives the winning slot from randomness to verify it matches. Let me also look at what the RoundSettled event looks like on-chain to know the fields."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1003,"cache_read_input_tokens":58334,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1003},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d59010d9-1bac-40d3-83bc-cafa01465d5f","uuid":"8f3545cc-5bf2-4821-8b2f-c39e62d91f3f"}
